# Company brain repos are LF-canonical on disk. Git is the database (invariant 2) and documents are
# plain markdown that render identically on every platform (invariant 3), so line endings must never
# vary by operator OS. This keeps a stock Windows install (core.autocrlf=true) from materializing CRLF
# working trees - which would make the sync engine's byte-for-byte conflict backups diverge from the
# operator's file (invariant 8). The client's SyncEngine also pins autocrlf=false on its own git ops;
# this file is the belt-and-suspenders for any other git access to a provisioned repo.
* text=auto eol=lf
